What is 6G and what its gonna be
•	6G huge shift from 5G.
•	Need 1 Tbps speeds and millions of IoT devices per km2.
•	Ground and satellite systems together for global coverage.
•	Move to O-RAN architecture.
•	Old way was locked hardware/software from one vendor.
•	O-RAN splits hardware and software so different vendors work together.
•	AI runs the network using controllers.
•	xApps for fast tasks and rApps for long tasks.
•	Apps automate resource stuff and signal beam routing.

Networks no longer behind wall
•	Open design is flexible but has bad security.
•	Old security used castle and moat where inside was safe.
•	6G has virtual cloud and too many devices so no physical boundary.
•	Attackers use weak IoT to get in and move around.

AML Threats
•	AI controls network so ML models are the targets.
•	New field called adversarial machine learning or AML.
•	Evasion attack: add tiny noise to data during use.
•	Noise tricks model into making errors like bad signal calc.
•	Data poisoning: secretly change data used to train AI.
•	Clean label attack: poisoned data looks normal to humans but breaks AI logic.

Zero Trust and AI Defense
•	Network wall failed so 6G needs Zero Trust Architecture.
•	Rule: no user or device trusted by default.
•	Every request checked based on behavior and context.
•	Checking millions of devices in ms impossible with old rules.
•	Use AI as core trust algorithm for speed.
•	ML monitors habits and traffic for dynamic trust scores.

Explainable AI 
•	AI is black box so reasoning is hidden.
•	Admins need to know why a connection was blocked.
•	Explainable AI frameworks decode the complex models.
•	Helps operators trust the automation and fix the system.


